# Project Context
You are building a Modern React Application using Vite, Tailwind CSS v4, and Firebase.

# Tech Stack & Best Practices

## Frontend (React + Vite)
- Use Functional Components with Hooks only.
- Use `jsx` extension for component files.
- Avoid `default` exports; use named exports (e.g., `export const Hero = () => {}`).
- STRICT: Use Tailwind CSS v4 for all styling.
  - Do NOT use `@apply` in CSS files. Use utility classes directly in JSX.
  - Use the new `<div class="shadow-sm">` syntax (no config file needed for standard values).
- Performance: Use `React.lazy` and `Suspense` for heavy routes.
- State Management: Keep state local where possible; use Context only for global data (Auth).

## Styling (Tailwind v4)
- Use standard Tailwind colors (e.g., `bg-blue-500`, `text-slate-900`).
- For "Glassmorphism", use: `backdrop-blur-md bg-white/10 border border-white/20`.
- Responsive design: Mobile-first (`w-full md:w-1/2`).

## Backend (Firebase)
- Use Modular SDK (v9+) imports only:
  - Good: `import { getAuth, signInWithEmailAndPassword } from "firebase/auth";`
  - Bad: `import firebase from "firebase/compat/app";`
- Security: NEVER hardcode API keys in the code. Use `import.meta.env.VITE_API_KEY`.

## AI Component Generation (21.dev style)
- When asked to generate UI, prioritize "Shadcn-like" clean aesthetics.
- Use lucid-react for icons if needed (install if requested).